The SQL Server (Transact-SQL) OR Operator is used to combine multiple conditions in a WHERE clause of SQL Server statement. 
It displays a record if any the conditions separated by OR operator is true.

Syntax
The syntax for using OR operator in SQL Server (Transact-SQL) is given below:

SELECT column1, column2, column3, ...
FROM table_name
WHERE condition1 OR condition2 OR condtion3 ....;

Example:

To select all records of the Employee table where Salary is greater than 2800 or Age is less than 25, the query is given below.

SELECT * FROM Employee
WHERE Salary > 2800 OR Age < 25;
